      "content": "The concerns raised by those advocating for traditional views are based on established biological understanding and the principle of age-appropriate education. From a scientific standpoint, the focus of early education is on concrete facts, and introducing complex, evolving social theories about gender is a pedagogical mismatch. These concerns are not merely \"old-fashioned ideas\"; they are rooted in the observable reality of human biology and the established role of schools.",
      "source": "target",
